In January, Lifetime revealed it is working on a movie about the relationship between Prince Harry and Meghan Markle The film, entitled Harry & Meghan: A Royal Romance, will chronicle their courtship, their first date, how they kept their romance under wraps and the global media attention surrounding their relationship. Hot on the heels of announcing the leads, the first teaser trailer for the movies has been released. Newcomer Murray Fraser (The Loch) will play Harry and Parisa Fitz-Henley will play Meghan. READ MORE: Prince Harry to marry Meghan Markle The 22-second clip, set to Callum Scott’s You Are the Reason, shows various scenes, from their first meeting to when Harry popped the question and even a bedroom scene. Meghan can be heard asking Harry: “Tell me something real.” He replies: “I don’t want my life to be this perfect royal picture. I just need you.” – Channel24